popupAnnouncement.ctaText: Discover MetaMask Portfolio today. Track and manage your web3 assets in one place!

childMarkdownRemark.html:
Getting Started

Welcome to MetaMask Institutional, were excited to have you onboard.

To start the onboarding process, please check your email inbox. You should have an invite to the address you provided during the sign-up process.

As the administrator for your organization, you will be required to input your email and password. Please note that the administrator will be the primary point of contact for the organization. Administrators will then be able to add team members.

If you have not yet downloaded the browser extension, or if youre going through the onboarding process on a new device, you will be prompted to do so. Please ensure that you do not have any other MetaMask wallet extensions installed on your browser while onboarding.

Once the extension is downloaded and installed, you will be prompted to set up MetaMask Institutional. Please select the Custodial and Self-Custodial option.

Next you will see a list of MMIs custodian partners. Please click on Fireblocks.

This will redirect you back to the familiar Fireblocks console.

Once here, please navigate to the Web3 Access tab on the left hand panel.

Next, click on Connect MetaMask Institutional button on the top right hand corner of the screen. You will see a pop up prompting you to select which vault you would like to connect to MMI. Please make your selection, then hit Connect.

This will trigger the MMI extension to pop up. Please hit Confirm and select the accounts you would like to connect to your MMI wallet.

Your Fireblocks and MMI accounts should now be set up. You can close the pop up and return to the MMI onboarding page.

If you would like to add additional team members to your organisation during the Early Access period, please let us know and we will enable their access.

With set up complete, you will be directed to the portfolio dashboard page where you can begin accessing web3.
Answers to commonly asked questions

modules.title: Fireblocks user guide FAQs > Fireblocks Beta

childMarkdownRemark.html: Fireblocks Early Access

modules.question: How do I get started with early access to the MetaMask Institutional and Fireblocks integration?

childMarkdownRemark.html: Fireblocks has emailed all users of its MetaMask fork an invitation to obtain early access to the MMI x Fireblocks integration. The MetaMask Institutional (MMI) team will give 25 organizations early access to the integration, and will reach out to each customer who has signed up to confirm their participation. All Early Access Program participants will have a dedicated onboarding session with the MMI team.

modules.question: Will all early access users receive the special conditions mentioned in the Fireblocks invitation?

childMarkdownRemark.html: Yes, everyone who has indicated interest to participate in the Early Access Programme will receive a 12 month subscription to MMI free of charge. Fees for other services, such as Consensys Staking (should a customer choose to use this service) will still apply.

modules.question: How will using MMI  differ from using other Fireblocks wallet offerings?

childMarkdownRemark.html:
You will be able to access web3 protocols via MetaMask Institutional in the same way that you use the MetaMask fork or WalletConnect options today. MMI maintains parity with MetaMask so you will have all of the experiences you are familiar with from MetaMask along with additional features including our portfolio management dashboard, compliance, staking marketplace and reporting.

When transacting, the experience should be identical to that of the traditional MetaMask flow. However, the confirmation window will not broadcast the transaction directly to mainnet. Instead it will trigger the existing approval processes you have established with your Fireblocks wallets.

modules.question: How do I connect my Fireblocks wallets to MMI?

childMarkdownRemark.html:
The good news is that our standard integration processes allows you to link the two platforms with a straightforward Connect to MMI button.

Should you need assistance with account activation, the MMI team can help guide you through the onboarding process, perform a tailored product demonstration, and answer any questions you may have. Please get in touch with your sales point of contact for this option.

Lastly, all users will need to fill out this brief KYC form.

modules.question: How do I invite users to my organization?

childMarkdownRemark.html:
For early access users, the MMI team will assist in adding users to your organizations.

To do so, please contact the Product Team or your Business Development Point of Contact with the list of users to be added to your organization.
Overview

modules.question: How does MetaMask Institutional (MMI) differ from MetaMask?

childMarkdownRemark.html:
MMI differs from MetaMask because it offers institution-required custody integrations alongside compliance, monitoring, and reporting tools on its portfolio dashboard.

  • Our custody and self-custody integrations allow multi-user access to an organization's wallet address(es).
  • Our compliance features include pre- and post-trade KYT risk assessment on smart contract addresses and DeFi pools.
  • Our highly performant set of APIs power the analytics to support price, balance, and portfolio attribution performance.

We enable organizations to interact with all of web3 by supporting the entire transaction lifecycle.

modules.question: Which networks does MMI support?

childMarkdownRemark.html: Similar to MetaMask, MMI supports all EVM chains. As a caveat, custodial account chain support is in part determined by the custodian you choose to work with. In January 2022, MMI launched custodian account multi-chain capabilitiesunlocking custodian account access to all EVM-compatible L2s and sidechains, which means MMI supports custodians in being able to have multi-chain access.

modules.question: Which tokens does MMI Support?

childMarkdownRemark.html: MMI supports ERC-20, ERC-721, and ERC-1155 token types, just as MetaMask does. However, access to specific tokens are determined by your custodians token support framework.

modules.question: Is there a minimum AUM requirement to use MMI?

childMarkdownRemark.html: We have no minimum AUM requirement to use MMI. There might be qualifying criteria or considerations that are Custody partner specific. We strive to serve every organization on the planet as they make their foray to Web3.

modules.question: How do I get started?

childMarkdownRemark.html:
Post-Beta, to get started, users can request access and, if needed, schedule a time with one of our sales team members.

The MMI team will be reaching out to all Beta participants proactively to walk them through this process in a guided session. (See Fireblocks-MMI Beta section below)

modules.question: Does MMI work with DAOs?

childMarkdownRemark.html: Yes. MMI supports many DAOs and Foundations. We look forward to mutually supporting these with Fireblocks and ideating new ways to serve their unique requirements.

modules.question: How much does MMI cost?

childMarkdownRemark.html:
Metamask Institutional has a standard monthly subscription fee based on the Assets Under Deployment (AUD) to the MMI wallet.

Please request access to find out more.

Further cost structures are determined by the custodian you choose to work. We recommend working directly with your custodian to determine these costs.

modules.question: How long does it take to onboard from start to finish?

childMarkdownRemark.html: Onboarding with MMI typically takes a few business days. The time frame is in part determined by the custodian you choose to work with. Your custodian might have separate onboarding processes that may need to be completed before they can activate your access.

modules.question: How do I connect my custodian account?

childMarkdownRemark.html: Within your Fireblocks platform/interface there will be a simple button to connect your custodian account with MMI. You can then select from the list of wallets you have created in your custodian account within MMI.

modules.question: How does MMI work with my fund administrator, auditor, and tax consultant?

childMarkdownRemark.html: MMI offers Portfolio Snapshots that generates a read-only view of your organizations holdings and transactions over a given timeframe. You can download the snapshot data from the dashboard into a .csv file or share a link with fund admins, LPs, or other third-parties to highlight valuation and transaction history. All historical on chain transactions since inception can also be downloaded in csv file from the Transaction Snapshots feature.

modules.question: Does MMI do any P&L calculations especially for DeFi positions?

childMarkdownRemark.html: Yes this is now available with the Portfolio Dashboard home screen. You can choose to view P&L or performance attribution for your DeFi positions.

modules.question: How does Swaps in MMI differ from UniSwap or 1Inch?

childMarkdownRemark.html:
MetaMask Swaps sources liquidity from the widest sources in the market, including Uniswap, AirSwap, 0x API, 1inch.exchange, Paraswap, and dex.ag.

We aim to provide the best quote in the market at all times, and we implement technical innovations to severely limit failure rates.

modules.title: Fireblocks user guide FAQs > Managing my Digital Assets

childMarkdownRemark.html: Managing my Digital Assets

modules.question: Can multiple users transact on the same wallet?

childMarkdownRemark.html: Yes, MMI allows organizations to filter and connect any account in the wallet from their custodian. This means users on different browser extensions can access the same wallets and accounts within.

modules.question: Can I access positions across multiple custodians on the same MMI platform?

childMarkdownRemark.html: Yes, MMI provides an aggregated view of your DeFi portfolio across all the accounts in the wallet, across custodians.

modules.question: How are my transactions sent to Mainnet?

childMarkdownRemark.html: After a transaction is confirmed in the extension, transaction details are sent to the custodian, where it can be approved and signed. The transaction is then broadcast to Mainnet from the custodian account.

modules.question: How do I receive transaction status updates from MMI?

childMarkdownRemark.html: The MMI SDK receives status updates from the custodian via a webhook so that transaction status and transaction activity are updated within the extension.

modules.question: Will all my token holdings in my custody account be reflected within my MMI wallet?

childMarkdownRemark.html: MMI reflects all on-chain transactions, including the tokens of those transactions, within the wallet. You may need to Import token contracts into your MMI wallet.

modules.question: Does MetaMask Institutional provide any insurance coverage in the case of private keys being compromised or hacked?

childMarkdownRemark.html: MMI does not hold any private keys on behalf of the customer. Private key management is done at the custodian level, hence the custodian you choose to work with is responsible for private key security and recovery. Different custodians have different recovery protocols and insurance policies, best to check with your chosen custodian.

modules.question: Who can I contact if I experience any issues?

childMarkdownRemark.html: Our Customer Support team consists of experienced technical support engineers combined with a self-service online helpdesk platform that provides the current status and full history of each support request. Please refer to the customer support language outlined in the Subscription agreement.
